 in\nthe southwestern halo. The luminous material is transported by the disk wind,\nwhich can explain the different amounts of extra-planar HI, Halpha, and soft\nX-ray emission in the two halo parts. Future low-frequency radio observations\nwill provide the data to analyze the vertical velocity profile of galactic\nwinds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Dec 2008 19:21:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Feb 2009 16:26:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
